{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"nonsecular-arthritic-sidewinder","description":"# PR posture on the GitHub mirror: welcome-bot redirect + shepherded-patch intake (with pre-flight experiments)\n\n## Why\n\nPRs opened against the mirror can never merge. Silent-ignore is the one universally condemned posture (Gerrit's own mirror with PRs rotting unanswered; pre-archive AOSP). Peers split two ways: Chromium/Qt/torvalds flipped GitHub's native Feb-2026 `has_pull_requests: false` setting (zero-cost but silent — no redirect at the moment of attempt); LibreOffice/Wikimedia/OpenDev bot-close with a warm redirect. For a project that wants to convert the occasional drive-by into a repeat contributor, research recommends keeping PRs ENABLED as an intake channel: a bot answers instantly and the maintainer converts worthwhile patches to Gerrit (Wikimedia's \"ask someone to convert\" path; Gerrit's Forge Author permission preserves the contributor's authorship).\n\n## What\n\nDecision (research-grounded default; revisit trigger = PR volume ever exceeding what a solo maintainer can shepherd): keep PRs ENABLED + auto-answer bot.\n\n- Add `.github/workflows/lockdown.yml` using `dessant/repo-lockdown@v5` (verified actively maintained: v5.0.2 released 2026-05-23, NOT archived) triggered on `pull_request_target: types: [opened, reopened]` (the `reopened` type closes Wikimedia's reopen loophole, T374157). `close-pr: true`, `lock-pr: false` (LibreOffice pattern — the thread stays open for conversation).\n- Comment message per the convergent five-part skeleton: thank by name; \"read-only mirror, PRs can't merge here — this close is automatic, nothing is wrong with your change\"; deep-link Gerrit (GitHub OAuth sign-in) + `docs/your-first-change.md`; shepherded-patch escape hatch (attach `git format-patch` output to a GitHub issue); warm welcome-not-rejection tone (Wikimedia T249703 framing).\n- Publish the shepherded-patch policy in CONTRIBUTING.md (Qt's voice: allowed, explicitly slower and best-effort): contributor attaches `git format-patch -1` output (embeds name/email/message so authorship is preserved exactly; plain diff acceptable with credit info) to an issue; maintainer applies with `git am` (author = contributor, committer = shepherd), amends the `rebar-ticket:` trailer in (message-only change, authorship untouched), pushes `refs/for/main`, drives review; `Co-authored-by:` only when the shepherd substantially rewrites.\n- Update the GitHub repo description to carry the mirror banner: \"Read-only mirror — code review at https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com\".\n\nPre-flight experiments (complete BEFORE the workflow lands; record each outcome as a ticket comment):\n- [E1] Scratch-repo test of `has_pull_requests: false` fork-side UX (what does a fork owner actually see in July 2026?) — documents the rejected alternative and informs the revisit trigger.\n- [E2] Admin read of Gerrit ACLs (JoeOakhartNava identity): confirm Forge Author is granted to Registered Users on the rebar project (Gerrit default, but hardened installs may differ) — required for authorship-preserving shepherding. If absent, file the ACL change.\n- [E3] Audit `.github/workflows/*` (gerrit-verify.yaml, mirror-guard.yml, reconcile-bridge*.yml, test.yml) for `pull_request`-event dependencies so the posture change breaks no existing automation.\n- [E4] Decide + document the `rebar-ticket:` trailer policy for shepherded patches (external patches won't reference a resolving ticket; default: shepherd creates/uses a ticket and amends the trailer in).\n\n## Scope\n\nIN: lockdown workflow + message text, CONTRIBUTING.md shepherding section, repo description, experiments E1–E4.\nOUT: GerritBot-style automatic PR→Gerrit import — explicit non-goal: only Go operates one, the official gerrit github-pullrequest plugin is dormant, and even at Go's scale bridged PRs merge at ~34% vs ~78% native; wrong cost/benefit below Go scale. Record with rationale.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A test PR from a non-collaborator fork receives the welcome comment and is closed (not locked) within ~1 minute.\n- [ ] The message names Gerrit + the first-change doc + the patch fallback and reads as a welcome, not a rejection.\n- [ ] E1–E4 outcomes recorded as ticket comments; Forge Author confirmed granted (or the ACL change filed and linked).\n- [ ] CONTRIBUTING.md documents the shepherded-patch path including authorship preservation, the trailer policy, and the best-effort caveat.\n- [ ] GerritBot-style auto-import recorded as an explicit non-goal with rationale.","id":"3b51-5bff-2d41-44c8","parent_id":"fc2a-9fa5-def6-4e68","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"PR posture on the GitHub mirror: welcome-bot redirect + shepherded-patch intake (pre-flight experiments)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783628665467488001,"uuid":"b576118c-63cf-47c6-81df-b332e757a462"}